The Open Services Group comprises of various Special Interest Groups (SIGs) and Working Groups (WG) which focus on various sub projects. Every sub project is maintained in a GitHub repository of its own. The project activities and contributions are tracked via GitHub issues and Pull Requests(PRs). 

## Data Collected

The various SIGs and its respecitve sub projects are defined [here](https://github.com/open-services-group/community/blob/main/sigs.yaml) and are as follows:

* **SIG Data Science** - Covers all aspects of Data Science and Machine Learning as it pertains to the open services group. It comprises of the following sub projects:
  * **OS Climate**
  * **Metrics**
  * **Operate First Data Science Community**

* **SIG Community Experience** - To nurture a sustainable community by stabilizing and growing it through delivering good quality services using the data driven approach.

* **SIG Services** - Oversee, steer and organize involvement and commitment of new and existing services. It comprises of the following sub projects:
  * **Peribolos-as-a-service**

* **WG BYON** -  The goal of this WG is to create a service that implements the Bring Your Own Notebook (BYON) MVP in the context of Open Data Hub. It comprises of the following sub project:
  * **BYON**

* **WG DevSecOps** - The goal of this working group is to enable operations of an instance of data science tooling as a service utilizing ODH.

The data is collected for the above mentioned SIGs/projects.
